  <div class="views-field-title">
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../library/chinafaqs-renewable-energy-china-overview-0">ChinaFAQs: Renewable Energy In China - An Overview</a></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-image-fid">
                <span class="field-content"><img src="../files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/ChinaFAQs_Renewable_Energy_Overview-1.jpg" alt="" title="" width="93" height="120" class="imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default"/></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-library-file-fid">
                <div class="field-content"><div class="filefield-file"><img class="filefield-icon field-icon-application-pdf"  alt="application/pdf icon" src="../sites/all/modules/filefield/icons/application-pdf.png" /><a href="../files/chinainfo/ChinaFAQs_Renewable_Energy_Overview_0.pdf" type="application/pdf; length=310393">ChinaFAQs_Renewable_Energy_Overview.pdf</a></div></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p><b>Key Points</b></p>

<ul><blockquote><blockquote>
<li>Currently, China gets about 9% of its total primary energy from non-fossil sources. Official targets aim to increase that share to at least 11.4 % in 2015 and 15% in 2020.</li>

<li>Solar Power: China is the world‚Äôs largest producer and exporter of solar cells (PVs).</li></blockquote></blockquote></ul></div>
